entry: Engine oil analysis shows high level of copper.
Magneto drop on left mag is 25 RPM above limit.
Crack found on #3 cylinder exhaust riser.
NAV/COM radio display is missing segments.
Left main tire shows excessive wear on inner side.
Right flap actuator showing signs of hydraulic fluid seep.
ADF needle unresponsive to test signal.
Pitot heat inoperative during ground check.
Compass correction card missing.
Shimmy damper needs servicing, nose wheel vibration on rollout.
Spark plugs fouled with oil residue.
Transponder fails to reply in Mode C.
Corrosion found on battery terminals.
Windshield crazing obstructing forward view.
Fuel strainer inspection revealed significant debris.
Mixture cable is stiff and difficult to adjust.
ELT battery past its replacement date.
Landing light bulb burnt out.
Seatbelt webbing is frayed.
Vacuum pump suction gauge reading is low.
